On 12/13/03 9:24 AM, "Christopher Flesher" <cflesher1(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> 1) I have a 73 type IV Progressive..how do I know what displacement it is?  I
> know that it is not the original but from a later year..how do I know if it's
> a 1700/1800/2000?  Can I look up the # off the engine to find out what year it
> is and will that be the answer?

On the fan shroud you'll find an engine number. The letter it starts with is
an indicator of the displacement:

http://www.tunacan.net/t4/reference/case.htm

The heads are also numbers in them for indentification:

http://www.tunacan.net/t4/tour/pics/heads/1.7-rockerbox.jpg
http://www.tunacan.net/t4/reference/cylhead.htm

> 2) also, just wondering..what is the diff. between the 1600 upright and the
> Type IV's (besides displacement)..what makes them "upright?"

A lot more torque.

